  "texts": [
    "Due to the broad applicability of probabilistic inference, improving key figures of merit, such as probabilistic flips per second (sampling throughput) and energy-delay product for this task are extremely important.",
    "To demonstrate this idea, we evaluate probabilistic inference on a probabilistic version of the full adder (FA) 45 as shown in Fig. 2a.",
    "The truth table of the FA is given in Fig. 2b.",
    "The FA performs 1-bit binary addition and it has three inputs (A, B, Carry in = C in) and two outputs (Sum = S, and Carry out = C out).",
    "The probabilistic FA can be described in a 5 p-bit, fully connected network (Fig. 2a)."
